* A Unix epoch time value with an associated reading from the elapsed realtime clock. * When representing a device's system clock time, the Unix epoch time can be obtained using {@link * System#currentTimeMillis()}. The Unix epoch time might also come from an external source * depending on usage. * *

The elapsed realtime clock can be obtained using methods like {@link * SystemClock#elapsedRealtime()} or {@link SystemClock#elapsedRealtimeClock()}. * * @hide
